Thai Red Curry

=== Req (4portionen): ===
300 g Sojageschnetzeltes
400ml Kokosmilch
Frischer Koreander
Frischer Basilikum
Bambussprossen
120g Prinzessbohnen
120g Süßkartoffel
Limettensaft
2 Schalotten

Ingwer
Gemüsebrühe
Fischsauce
Knoblauch
Kaffir-Limettenblätter 
Currypaste (Mae Ploy)
Palmzucker
ZitronengrasPaste
Brokkoli
2 Karotten

=== Zutaten für 4 Portionen: ===
4 EL Currypaste
2 	Schalotte(n)
2 	Knoblauchzehe(n)
300 g Sojageschnetzeltes
400 ml 	Kokosmilch
250 ml leichte Gemüsebrühe
120g Prinzessbohnen
120g Süßkartoffel
120g Brokkoli
2 Karotten
1 EL Zitronengraspaste
1 EL 	Fischsauce
1 EL 	Palmzucker
2 TL Ingwer

1 große Chilischote
5 Kaffir-Limettenblätter

  try:
  1 TL 	Koriander - Samen
  1 TL 	Kreuzkümmel

Frischer Koreander, Basilikum

=== Zubereitung ===


Schalotten Kochen, nicht anbraten!

Heat oil in a heavy based skillet or pot over medium high heat.
Add curry paste (and garlic, ginger and lemongrass Extras, if using) and cook for 2 to 3 minutes until it mostly "dries out" 
Add chicken broth and coconut milk, mix to dissolve paste.
Curry in a jar seasonings: Add 1 tsp fish sauce, 1 tsp sugar, no salt.

Add kaffir lime leaves. Mix then bring to simmer.
Add chicken, stir then lower heat to medium so it's bubbling gently. Cook 7 minutes.
Add eggplants, cook 5 minutes until soft.
Taste sauce. Add fish sauce or salt for more saltiness, sugar for sweetness.
Add snow peas, cook 2 minutes until a bit softened, then stir through basil and lime juice. 
Sauce should have reduced but will still be a be on the thin side, not thick - that's how it's should be. DO NOT keep simmering - sauce will darken.
